  "text": "Despite the important role of NPDs in leading and managing Olympic programs, to date, only a limited body of research exists pertaining to these figures. To elaborate, Fletcher and Arnold [CITATION_1] interviewed NPDs and identified four overarching areas of best practice when leading and managing teams in preparation for Olympic competition: developing a vision, managing operations, leading people, and creating a culture. Subsequent research has extended the findings on development and dissemination of an organizational vision;",
